The way they describe it, they send light down a cable, then watch for the =
reflection to come back to them.
The reflection should look the same with every single pulse of light, unles=
s something affects it, which in this case would be the vibrations of sound=
.
So it should pick up sound along the entire length of cable, which would re=
turn a lot of ambient noise if you're trying to hear inside someone's house=
 from all the way back at a utility company.
I don't know how good their audio filtering abilities are, but it seems lik=
e wherever you take measurements can't be too far from what you want to hea=
r.
